From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000008 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Emil Renner Berthing <emil.renner.berthing@canonical.com>
Date: Tue, 5 Aug 2025 19:23:15 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 08/11] riscv: sbi: stub GET_MVENDORID/MARCHID/MIMPID for VSRVES01

The custom in-house SBI firmware on the VLSI VSRVES01 SoC does not
implement the SBI base extension calls GET_MVENDORID, GET_MARCHID or
GET_MIMPID.  Worse, it halts the hart when an unknown SBI function is
invoked instead of returning SBI_ERR_NOT_SUPPORTED, so we cannot
probe at runtime.

As a temporary workaround, hard-code the three accessors to return 0.
This is safe: the callers (cpuinfo, kvm hypervisor probe, errata
matching) all treat 0 as "unknown" and continue.

A cleaner upstream-quality fix would call SBI_EXT_BASE_PROBE first
and only issue the real ecall if the function is reported as
supported; that requires more plumbing and is left for a follow-up.

Origin: esmil/linux vsrv branch 4fc8fb320405

Signed-off-by: Emil Renner Berthing <emil.renner.berthing@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Sungjoon Moon <sumoon@seoulsaram.org>
---
 arch/riscv/kernel/sbi.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/riscv/kernel/sbi.c b/arch/riscv/kernel/sbi.c
--- a/arch/riscv/kernel/sbi.c
+++ b/arch/riscv/kernel/sbi.c
@@ -570,19 +570,19 @@ static inline long sbi_get_firmware_version(void)
 
 long sbi_get_mvendorid(void)
 {
-	return __sbi_base_ecall(SBI_EXT_BASE_GET_MVENDORID);
+	return 0; /* __sbi_base_ecall(SBI_EXT_BASE_GET_MVENDORID); */
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(sbi_get_mvendorid);
 
 long sbi_get_marchid(void)
 {
-	return __sbi_base_ecall(SBI_EXT_BASE_GET_MARCHID);
+	return 0; /* __sbi_base_ecall(SBI_EXT_BASE_GET_MARCHID); */
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(sbi_get_marchid);
 
 long sbi_get_mimpid(void)
 {
-	return __sbi_base_ecall(SBI_EXT_BASE_GET_MIMPID);
+	return 0; /* __sbi_base_ecall(SBI_EXT_BASE_GET_MIMPID); */
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(sbi_get_mimpid);
 
